ity, dealt with the spiritual concerns of a society undergoing great change. Their philosophical orientation known as "Seishinshugi" ("cultivating spirituality") provides a set of principles that prioritized personal, subjective experience as the basis for religious understanding.In addition to providing access to work generally unavailable in English, this volume also includes both a contextualizing introduction and introductions to each figure included.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aPure Land Buddhism. 0aReligious lifexBuddhism. 0aShin (Sect). 4aAsian Studies : Asian Religion and Philosophy. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aAsian Studies : Japanese Studies. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Buddhism. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aRELIGION / Buddhism / General (see also PHILOSOPHY / Buddhist).2bisacsh1 aBlum, Mark L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlum, Mark L., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBragt, Jan Van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDaiei, Kaneko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aManshi, Kiyozawa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRhodes, Robert F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRhodes, Robert F., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRijin, Yasuda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRyøjin, Soga, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWatt, Paul B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWatt, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978